<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Central Texas, Up Close</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #151411;
      --bg-soft: #1d1b17; 
      --card: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      --card-strong: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
      --text: #efe9dc;
      --muted: #c0b7a4;
      --line: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
      --accent: #c99b49;
      --accent-2: #7aa68f;
      --shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
      --radius: 22px;
      --radius-sm: 16px;
      --content: 1240px;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      color: var(--text);
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(201,155,73,0.16), transparent 28%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 80% 10%, rgba(122,166,143,0.12), transparent 25%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, #191712 0%, #12110f 100%);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
    img { display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; }

    .container {
      width: min(calc(100% - 32px), var(--content));
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .skip-link {
      position: absolute;
      left: 16px;
      top: -48px;
      padding: 10px 14px;
      background: #fff;
      color: #111;
      border-radius: 10px;
      z-index: 1000;
    }

    .skip-link:focus { top: 16px; }

    header {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 20;
      backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
      background: rgba(21,20,17,0.68);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .nav {
      min-height: 72px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 16px;
    }

    .brand {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 14px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      font-size: 0.82rem;
    }

    .logo {
      width: 42px;
      height: 42px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 35% 35%, rgba(201,155,73,0.95), rgba(201,155,73,0.15) 55%, transparent 56%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 70% 70%, rgba(122,166,143,0.8), rgba(122,166,143,0.08) 50%, transparent 51%),
        rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }

    .nav-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .nav-links a {
      padding: 10px 14px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      color: var(--muted);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      border: 1px solid transparent;
      transition: 180ms ease;
      min-height: 44px;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .nav-links a:hover,
    .nav-links a:focus-visible {
      color: var(--text);
      border-color: var(--line);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
      outline: none;
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 72px 0 40px;
    }

    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
      gap: 28px;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .panel {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.06), rgba(255,255,255,0.03));
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 28px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .hero-copy {
      padding: 34px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 24px;
      min-height: 100%;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.16em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .dot {
      width: 8px;
      height: 8px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--accent);
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px rgba(201,155,73,0.12);
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 5vw, 5.8rem);
      line-height: 0.96;
      letter-spacing: -0.05em;
      max-width: 10ch;
    }

    .hero-copy p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1.03rem;
      max-width: 58ch;
    }

    .hero-notes {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 14px;
    }

    .note {
      padding: 16px;
      border-radius: 18px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    }

    .note strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .note span {
      display: block;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.94rem;
    }

    .hero-image {
      min-height: 560px;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      isolation: isolate;
    }

    .hero-image img {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      object-position: center 38%;
      filter: saturate(0.95) contrast(1.02);
      transform: scale(1.04);
    }

    .hero-image::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background:
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.06), rgba(0,0,0,0.42)),
        linear-gradient(120deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.00) 42%, rgba(0,0,0,0.45) 100%);
    }

    .hero-caption {
      position: absolute;
      left: 20px;
      right: 20px;
      bottom: 20px;
      z-index: 1;
      padding: 18px 18px 16px;
      border-radius: 18px;
      background: rgba(10,10,10,0.46);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.14);
      backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    }

    .hero-caption strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    .hero-caption span {
      color: #ddd2bf;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    section {
      padding: 28px 0 44px;
    }

    .section-head {
      display: flex;
      align-items: end;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }

    .section-head h2 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 2.8vw, 2.6rem);
      line-height: 1.02;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .section-head p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      max-width: 62ch;
    }

    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
      gap: 18px;
    }

    .card {
      grid-column: span 4;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.055), rgba(255,255,255,0.03));
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      overflow: hidden;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      transition: transform 220ms ease, border-color 220ms ease, background 220ms ease;
      content-visibility: auto;
      contain-intrinsic-size: 800px;
    }

    .card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-4px);
      border-color: rgba(201,155,73,0.35);
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.07), rgba(255,255,255,0.03));
    }

    .card.tall { grid-column: span 4; }
    .card.wide { grid-column: span 8; }

    .image-wrap {
      position: relative;
      aspect-ratio: var(--ratio, 4 / 5);
      overflow: hidden;
      background: #111;
      cursor: zoom-in;
    }

    .image-wrap::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0,0,0,0) 60%, rgba(0,0,0,0.18) 100%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .image-wrap img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      object-position: var(--pos, center center);
      transition: transform 800ms cubic-bezier(.16,1,.3,1), filter 220ms ease;
      filter: saturate(1.02) contrast(1.03);
    }

    .card:hover .image-wrap img {
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }

    .content {
      padding: 20px 20px 22px;
    }

    .kicker {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 0.74rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    h3 {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      line-height: 1.05;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .desc {
      margin: 0 0 16px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.98rem;
    }

    .meta {
      display: grid;
      gap: 10px;
    }

    .meta div {
      padding-top: 10px;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    }

    .meta strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: #e9d9bb;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    .meta span {
      display: block;
      color: #d7cfbf;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .closing {
      padding: 18px 22px 70px;
    }

    .closing-box {
      padding: 28px;
      border-radius: 28px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      background:
        linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.06), rgba(255,255,255,0.02)),
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(201,155,73,0.18), transparent 24%);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }

    .closing-box h2 {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2vw, 2.2rem);
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .closing-box p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      max-width: 72ch;
    }

    .lightbox {
      position: fixed;
      inset: 0;
      display: none;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 18px;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.82);
      z-index: 100;
    }

    .lightbox.open { display: flex; }

    .lightbox img {
      max-width: min(94vw, 1400px);
      max-height: 86vh;
      border-radius: 18px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
      background: #111;
    }

    .lightbox button {
      position: absolute;
      top: 18px;
      right: 18px;
      min-width: 44px;
      min-height: 44px;
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
      color: white;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1100px) {
      .hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .hero-image { min-height: 420px; }
      .card, .card.wide, .card.tall { grid-column: span 6; }
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .nav { align-items: flex-start; padding-block: 14px; flex-direction: column; }
      .nav-links { width: 100%; }
      .nav-links a { flex: 1 1 auto; justify-content: center; }
      .hero { padding-top: 34px; }
      .hero-copy { padding: 22px; }
      .hero-notes { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .section-head { align-items: start; flex-direction: column; }
      .card, .card.wide, .card.tall { grid-column: span 12; }
      .closing { padding-bottom: 44px; }
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      html { scroll-behavior: auto; }
      * { transition: none !important; animation: none !important; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <a class="skip-link" href="#gallery">Skip to gallery</a>

  <header>
    <div class="container nav">
      <div class="brand">
        <div class="logo" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" aria-label="Central Texas logo">
            <path d="M5 16c2.4-3.8 4.9-6 7-6s4.6 2.2 7 6" />
            <path d="M4 18h16" />
            <path d="M12 5v8" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <span>Central Texas, Up Close</span>
      </div>

      <nav class="nav-links" aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="#intro">Intro</a>
        <a href="#gallery">Gallery</a>
        <a href="#closing">Closing</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main id="intro">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="panel hero-copy">
          <div>
            <div class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Nature portfolio</div>
            <h1>Austin seen at trail speed</h1>
          </div>

          <p>
            This gallery is built like a dusk walk through the Hill Country: limestone first,
            then creek light, then the small things that reward attention. The crops lean into
            intimacy, texture, and scale shifts, so each frame feels less like a record shot and
            more like a field note from Central Texas.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-notes">
            <div class="note">
              <strong>Art direction</strong>
              <span>Warm stone, low light, dark creek greens, and close studies of native detail.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="note">
              <strong>Through-line</strong>
              <span>Every image ties back to the limestone ecology, drought rhythm, and creek culture of Austin.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="note">
              <strong>Viewing tip</strong>
              <span>Click any image to open it larger.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="panel hero-image">
          <img src="IMG_9951.jpeg" alt="Small deer standing under stacked limestone ledges at dusk" loading="eager" width="896" height="1344" />
          <div class="hero-caption">
            <strong>The first scene sets the tone.</strong>
            <span>A deer, shadow, and limestone overhang turn the whole collection into an Austin twilight story.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="gallery">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2>Photo studies</h2>
          <p>
            Each card includes a short description, the main focal point, why it feels specifically Central Texas,
            and an Austin story that gives the image a local pulse.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid">

          <article class="card tall">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 4/6; --pos: 50% 34%;">
              <img src="IMG_9951.jpeg" alt="Deer standing beneath a limestone overhang" loading="lazy" width="896" height="1344" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">01 · Mammal and stone</span>
              <h3>Deer Under the Ledge</h3>
              <p class="desc">The crop turns the deer into a quiet witness inside a natural amphitheater of fractured limestone and dusk shadow.</p>
              <div class="meta">
                <div><strong>Focal point</strong><span>The deer is the emotional center, but the limestone shelf gives it drama and scale.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Central Texas tie</strong><span>This is classic Hill Country habitat: broken limestone, cedar shade, and wildlife moving most confidently at day’s edge.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Austin story</strong><span>Anyone who has walked Barton Creek or Bull Creek late in the evening knows this moment—the city feels far away, and suddenly you are sharing the trail with something older than Austin itself.</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card tall">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 4/6; --pos: 42% 48%;">
              <img src="IMG_9946.jpeg" alt="Shallow creek water moving over smooth limestone at dusk" loading="lazy" width="896" height="1344" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">02 · Water and shelf rock</span>
              <h3>Creek Shelf at Dusk</h3>
              <p class="desc">This image works because the tilt makes the water feel like it is slipping over the frame, as if the creek is pulling the viewer downstream.</p>
              <div class="meta">
                <div><strong>Focal point</strong><span>The main subject is the limestone creek bed itself—smooth, pale, and still holding a skin of moving water.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Central Texas tie</strong><span>Those shelves are part of the region’s visual language; they shape swimming holes, flash-flood channels, and the entire look of local creeks.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Austin story</strong><span>In Austin, creek rock is social architecture: kids climb it, runners cut across it, and after good rain the whole city seems to migrate back to stone and water.</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card wide">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 16/9; --pos: 26% 42%;">
              <img src="IMG_9961.jpeg" alt="Limestone overhang beside a reflective creek pool at sunset" loading="lazy" width="1240" height="930" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">03 · Overhang study</span>
              <h3>Stone Face, Quiet Water</h3>
              <p class="desc">The crop emphasizes the ledge on the left until it almost reads like a profile, giving the formation a watchful presence over the pool.</p>
              <div class="meta">
                <div><strong>Focal point</strong><span>The limestone overhang is the anchor, with the reflective water acting like a second, softer mirror of the same scene.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Central Texas tie</strong><span>Shaded ledges and creek pockets are where the Hill Country feels most sculptural; the land here is less rolling postcard and more carved geology.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Austin story</strong><span>Austin hikers love the obvious overlooks, but the best memories often come from these side-angle pockets where the creek quiets down and the stone starts to feel inhabited.</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card wide">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 16/9; --pos: 34% 52%;">
              <img src="IMG_9955.jpeg" alt="Green fern growing out of a limestone seam" loading="lazy" width="1240" height="930" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">04 · Seep ecology</span>
              <h3>Fern in the Limestone Seam</h3>
              <p class="desc">The crop makes the fern read like a miniature oasis, a small burst of softness against a canyon of hard stone.</p>
              <div class="meta">
                <div><strong>Focal point</strong><span>The fern cluster is the star, especially because it appears to be surviving from almost no soil at all.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Central Texas tie</strong><span>Shaded seeps and damp fractures in limestone are some of the few places where delicate greenery can persist through heat and exposure.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Austin story</strong><span>After rain on the Greenbelt, people talk about waterfalls, but the real secret is how the walls wake up—tiny ferns, moss, and seep plants make the rock look newly alive.</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card tall">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 4/6; --pos: 50% 40%;">
              <img src="IMG_9968.jpeg" alt="Close-up of pale winged seed clusters" loading="lazy" width="896" height="1344" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">05 · Seed architecture</span>
              <h3>Winged Seeds in Evening Light</h3>
              <p class="desc">This crop leans into the elegant tangle of the seed cluster, letting it feel almost drawn rather than photographed.</p>
              <div class="meta">
                <div><strong>Focal point</strong><span>The subject is the hanging seed whorl—thin, pale, and delicate against the dark background.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Central Texas tie</strong><span>Late spring and summer in Austin are full of these transitional details: flowers giving way to seed, heat turning abundance into survival strategy.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Austin story</strong><span>There is a very local pleasure in noticing the in-between stage of a plant, because Austin nature culture is not only about bloom season; it is about watching the whole cycle happen in real time.</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card tall">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 4/6; --pos: 55% 45%;">
              <img src="IMG_9930.jpeg" alt="Creekside plant with dark seed spikes and palmate leaves" loading="lazy" width="896" height="1344" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">06 · Creekside ornamental gone local</span>
              <h3>Vitex by the Water</h3>
              <p class="desc">The frame uses shallow depth and sunset haze to make the plant feel like a silhouette of memory rather than a catalog specimen.</p>
              <div class="meta">
                <div><strong>Focal point</strong><span>The main subject is the dark seed spike rising in front of the glowing creek background.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Central Texas tie</strong><span>Vitex shows up all over Austin as a heat-tolerant favorite; once you know its leaf shape and bloom spikes, you start seeing it at trail edges, medians, and old neighborhoods.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Austin story</strong><span>This feels like the Austin habit of blending planted and wild landscapes—garden species do not stay politely in gardens here, and the city’s ecology is full of overlap.</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card tall">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 4/5; --pos: 50% 42%;">
              <img src="IMG_9938.jpeg" alt="Tiny white flowers with dark red bracts in grasses" loading="lazy" width="1240" height="930" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">07 · Ground-level detail</span>
              <h3>Crimson-Bracted Creek Bloom</h3>
              <p class="desc">This is one of those photographs that rewards kneeling down; the crop gives a tiny plant the visual dignity of a portrait.</p>
              <div class="meta">
                <div><strong>Focal point</strong><span>The eye goes straight to the little cluster of white blossoms held by deep wine-colored bracts.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Central Texas tie</strong><span>Trailside flora here often lives at ankle height, hidden in grass, rock litter, and cedar duff—small enough to miss unless you slow all the way down.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Austin story</strong><span>Austin’s best nature walks often turn into scavenger hunts, because someone always stops the group with, “Wait, look at this tiny thing,” and the whole pace of the walk changes.</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card tall">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 4/6; --pos: 58% 45%;">
              <img src="IMG_9936.jpeg" alt="Purple bloom spike with soft green background" loading="lazy" width="896" height="1344" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">08 · Pollinator color</span>
              <h3>Purple Spray Against the Creek</h3>
              <p class="desc">The crop gives the bloom room to breathe, so the plant feels suspended in air with the creek fading into a soft green wash behind it.</p>
              <div class="meta">
                <div><strong>Focal point</strong><span>The purple flower cluster is the main attraction, bright enough to pull the entire image toward it.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Central Texas tie</strong><span>Purple flowering spikes feel especially Austin because they bridge ornamental planting and pollinator habitat in one gesture.</span></div>
                <div><strong>Austin story</strong><span>In many Austin yards and parks, purple blooms are summer traffic signs for bees and butterflies; even in heavy heat, they keep the landscape feeling active.</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="card tall">
            <div class="image-wrap" style="--ratio: 4/6; --pos: 52% 48%;">
              <img src="IMG_9931.jpeg" alt="Orange yellow black-eyed Susan wildflower" loading="lazy" width="896" height="1344" />
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="kicker">09 · Native brightness</span>
              <h3>Black-Eyed Susan, Solitary</h3>
